title: An Average Car
author: justin
text: metaphor poem by justin  11/2/09  â“an average carâ”  my family is an average car with some minor dents and scratches but still rolling along.   my dad is the steady steering wheel,  guiding us through complex obstacles that our family constantly faces.   my mom is the tough rubber around the metal frame of the tires,  absorbing all the bothersome bumps so that we can be comfortable.  my brother is the a. m.  radio,  providing continuous but sometimes annoying entertainment.    and i am the inconspicuous dome light,  that they donâ’t know is there until they need it.

title: The day I went nuts!
author: karlie
text: the day i went nuts! i got out of bed,   i walked down the street.  here are some animals,  that i did meet.   i met a moose,  whoâ’s name was frank.  but he jumped in a puddle,  and frank slowly sank.   i kept walking along,  and what i did see.  .  .   people jumping from buildings,  and chased by a chimpanzee.   that fat chimpanzee,  was wearing a hat.  and under his hat,  was a blue and purple cat!  the next thing i knew,  i felt colder indeed,  for a family of penguins,  were now on my feet!  the farther i walked,  the weirder things got.  owls were dancing,  i my schoolâ’s parking lot.   i ran all the way,  back to my house.  sleeping soundly on my bed,  was a green colored mouse.   he spoke in a language,  i couldnâ’t quite get,  but i thought,  i think iâ’ll keep him as a pet.   i woke up the next morning,  i walked down the street.  but i didnâ’t see… any animals i had met.   for show and tell,  that day at school.  i told my class my story,  and they thought it was cool.   i thought i had brought,  my pet mouse that day.  but it got out of my bag,  and then ran away.   i woke up the next morning,  i had,  had a dream,  about a moose and some penguins,  and a chimpanzee.   it was all a dream,  now my friends thought i was crazy.  it could happen again,  maybe?         by karlie pipher

title: Bird
author: karlie
text: squeak! caw! squeak! caw! says the headache giving bird.  squeak! caw! squeak! caw! i now must yell the word. . .  quiet! bird,  i'm trying to sleep.  i'll pluck off your feathers,  then tape up your beak.  he quieted down,  for a second or so.  squeak! caw! squeak! caw! here we go! quiet! bird,  i'm trying to sleep.  i'll pluck off your feathers,  then tape up your beak.  he quieted down,  for a second or so,  then he mimiced the words,  like this,  they go. . .  quiet! human,  i'm trying to sleep,  i'll pluck off your eyebrows,  then bite off your feet! a second of quiet,  and then the sound. . .  squeak! caw! squeak! caw! was all around.  quiet! bird,  i'm trying to sleep.  i'll pluck off your feathers,  then tape up your beak.  i was snoring,  and that's a warning.  i'll pluck off your eyebrows,  then bite off your feet.  the bird then snored,  and snored and snored.  squeak! caw! squeak! caw! then all aboard? the neighbors rushed in,  but there wasn't a boat.  squeak! caw! squeak! caw! they would send him afloat.  they plucked off his feathers,  aand taped up his beak,  and then they got a. . .  caw! caw! squeak! the neighbors yelled. . .  quiet! bird,  we're trying to sleep.  we've plucked off you feathers,  and taped up your beak! we'll send you away,  if you do it again,  send you to neverland,  with peter pan! tthe bird settled down,  he drank out of his cup.  caw! squeak! caw! squeak! now he had the hiccups.

title: The Quiet Guy
author: karlie
text: people think i cannot write,  said jimmy to his mom.  no one thinks that i can write,  except for my friend tom.  for show and tell,   kids bring thinks like,  jello in their shoes,  but instead i bring my poems,  and my friend get bored and blue.  when i go outside for recess,  with my books and my pen,  kids pick me up and spin me round,  then dare me to bawk like a hen.  in science they say,  hey quiet guy! give us your books,  or we'll make you cry.  so i gave up my books,  in dismay.  i hope i get them back,  someday.  there the meanest bunch of bullies,  in my entire school.  when i'm at home, they call me,  and tell me i'm a fool.  sometimes i want to punch them out,  although i know i can't.  for if i did,  i know i'd get,  a big kick in the pants! i had a dream about a plan,  to get all my books back.  to do so though,  i'd have to hide,  inside a potato sack.  so then next day when i went to school,  i hid inside a sack.  and while frank was busy in science,  ii hid in his backpack.  when the end of the day approached,  i didn't go on the bus.  i stayed inside the backpack,  unpack your bag frank.  you must! but frank was so lazy,  he fell fast asleep,  his mom came in with supper,  and made a loud noise,  beep! slowly frank woke up,  and then he ate his supper,  he fell right back to sleep,  he was now a big fat chubber! i quietly said in his ear,  your no longer mean to jimmy,  but if your mean,  i'll make sure,  that your really fat not skinny.  on monday when they went to school,  frank was a good friend,  to jimmy and the other nerds,  until the very end.

title: Real Dreams Real Reality
author: karmen
text: i step out the house to see,  my elderly neighbors playing croquet,   and beautiful large plateaus.  i spin a 360 to show the chauffeur   my new dress.  he opens the limousine door and helps me in  and weâ’re off! i step into the room i feel like a princess,  because everyoneâ’s attention is on me.  suddenly bouquets of flowers are being thrown my way.  someone i do not recognize tilts their beret at me  and says â“bonjour miss danseâ”? i looked at him squarely and said yes.  after we are done he asks in a formal way â“would you like an ã©clair?â”  i say with my proper etiquette â“yes i would. â” as we are eating i accidentally spill some of my pastry.  at that point and time i wanted to be a chameleon and fade in the background and camouflage myself.  i thought about leaving but before  i did i stored this memory in a sacred envelope in my mind.  then a sergeant in my brain asks me an important question.  do i really want to sacrifice this perfect day only because of a small spill? that question is playing simultaneously in my head like a broken cassette player.  my dream seemed real to me and you,   but the theater is closed,  and all the wonderful people in my dream-fantasy stand at the depot  to catch the next dream train for tomorrow.  as for me i am sitting in my homey chalet campaigning and waiting for a dream  as wonderful as todayâ’s.  maybe iâ’ll dream about a heroic cadet saving the world,  or  a formal,  beautiful,  arrogant,  ballet performance.  i do not know the future so i will wait for tomorrow and the parade of new hopes and dreams it brings me.

title: The Bouncing Ball
author: kasim
text: bounce bounce, goes the ball.   it lunges off the wall.  going up and down and side to side,  until it could not bounce any more.  then as it was picked up and hurled once more,  the ball soared through the air like a shooting star.  down it bounced,  spinning round and round.  as if it was going through a black hole with darkness everywhere.  has its journey ended? what more can it do? where else can it go? how much more can it bounce? flying like a meteor,  it dashes side to side,  with nowhere else to bounce but down.  it crashes to the ground,  forming a hole like a crater.  now with its life at an end,  the bouncing ball will bounce no more.

title: The Jabberwocky
author: kate
text: 'twas cool and the dead leaves did toss and turn in the breeze: all topsy-turvy were the squirrels and the bears sleeping.   ''beware the jabberwock my son! the teeth that crush,  the talons that grab! beware the peacock beast,  and avoid  the malignant hawk!''  he took his shining sword in hand: long time the peevish foe he sought- so rested he by the apple tree,  and stood awhile in thought.   and,  as in deep thought he stood,   the jabberwock with eyes of death,  came looming through the thick wood and roared as it came!  one,  two! one,  two! and back and forth the shining blade went clash! he left it slain,  and with its head he went running back.   ''and has thou killed the jabberwock? come to my arms my adventurous boy! o wonderful day! hurrah! hurray! he chuckled in his merriment.   'twas cool,  and the dead leaves did toss and turn in the breeze: all topsy-turvy were the squirrels  and the bears sleeping.

title: Where I'm From
author: katelynn
text: i am from the busy streets with tall glass buildings,  from the annoying little screeches of the millions of crows that like to sit on the tree right beside where i live.  i am from the smell of grannyâ’s sweet orange slices ( the candy ),  the stinky breath of sable that always surrounds me.  i am from tan skin with feathers in hair,  while dancing around the fire celebrating life.   i am from paddles and principals offices,   awaiting the punishment i may have.  i am from the nasty air that surrounds my father,  while my sister shakes her head in disappointment.  i am from the stomach that holds an unborn child,  that will soon be born from my fathers beloved.  i am from the scars that will lay forever on my sister.   i am from the chicken alfredo that fills my stomach at olive garden.  from the wet tears of where the red fern grows.  the one and only ivan,  a book filled with many amazing words  that explain the hardships of living a life an an ape.  i am from â“my mother never let me do this or let me have thatâ”.   i am from the bright yellow fuzz on balls that hit you.   i am from the homework club filled with many shrieks.   i am from one of many desks that cover the floor of mr.  jones room,   the hard working teacher that urged me to write this poem.

title: Cold (As before)
author: kathy
text: looking out my window,  wanting to drown in the afterglow of the night.  it's nice and warm in here,  makes me want to just disappear,  but i can't.  the rain slams against the tin roof.  leaving me cold as before.  you're somewhere,  you're drifting away,  which makes me miss you even more.  i sit curled up by the flames,  studying pictures,  ignoring the frames,  bringing back memories.  you aren't in any of these,  but you should be.  i should have taken a picture,   it would have lasted longer than you.  i stand in the rain,   as it blends with my tears,  leaving me cold as before.  i know out there,  but not with me.  that makes me miss you even more.  i don't want to cry,  that makes me sound so sad.  but i can't help it it's hard.  shouldn't have let you go alone,  i should have been there for you.  at the last did you scream? i can't help but wonder these things.  i wait for the rain,  to wash me away.  so i wont feel as cold as before,  are you there,  can you hear me? just letting you know,  i miss you even more.

title: Moon
author: katie
text: sitting in the black dull void above my head,  sits a friend who watches while i sleep in bed.  his milky white light tucks me in with gentle hands,  and sings to me a song about magical lands.  from the twinkleing stars a warm kiss brushes my cheek,  while i drift away to dream and seek.

title: The Wispy Wind
author: katie
text: drifting through the sunlit sky.  my life seems to float right by.   swimming through the clouds above.  gracefully running like a flying dove.   i tickle the grass with peevish fingers.  as i suddenly leave,  a sweet smell lingers.   dancing affably with the sun's shining light.  children chase me with great delight.   in the barren dark void of night,  i loom in the air out of sight.   i bathe in the moon's sparkling white ray.  i then alight form star to star and not stay.

title: My four legged friend
author: katie
text: i love docile dogs who are there to talk to when no one listens who brightens a lonely day who plays with you when you're all alone who keeps your secrets you can't share who greets you from a hard day of school who makes you laugh when you thought you wouldn't a dog that keeps you warm on a damp dark stormy night a dog that eases your troubled mind a dog who's a friend when you thought you had none a dog to cry on when nothing goes right.  a dog that will be there no matter what you do.   ~this poem is in honor of my dog alex who i knew since i was born.  she had to be put down on january 15th,  2004.  we miss you!

title: My Mind is Like...
author: katie

title: My Hero
author: katie
text: my hero may not be prince charming,  but he does know how to treat someone with respect.  my hero may not be a firefighter,   but he does save lives.  my hero may not be a doctor but he does make the pain disappear.  my hero may not be a charity,  but he gives as much as he can to people in need.  my hero may not be a saint,  but he does have a heart of gold.  my hero may not be a model,  but he looks his very best to me.  my hero may not be an actual hero with a cape,  but he is my hero.  my hero.

title: My Place

text: in my mind  there is a place a free place   in this place i sit in fields of  delicate gold flowers a blue bowl of sky above  clouds as fluffy as the ends of cue-tips drift past whiter than fresh snow here i know  i am free  exit my mind  and the gold is forgotten the blue fades to grey as  reality sets back in  grimy spouts shoot  water at my eyes  far missing its open target  the squeal of tires in the air smoke clouding my throat a thick layer of dust beneath my feet the cracked leather on which i sit and all i see are white heads bobbing to and fro in front of me  shiny cars ride by as i walk the way to school to church plum colored splotches cover my already  dark feet so its to the store for a new pair of shoes then back home again  but go to  my place that wonderland inside my head and all is quiet people of all sorts stand around me like a checkerboard as we bask in the morning sunlight smiles gleam as happiness overwhelms us no one is walking because there is no need why walk away from here?  in our dreams there is a place a free place our place this place

title: Ocean's Fun
author: katie
text: as the hours pass through the states we're looking forward to the upcoming dates.  sitting in the car for so many hours thinking of our huge sand towers.  and suddenly out the window i see sand and water,  just waiting for me.  unpacking is a mess,  but finally we settle in and head off to the beach where the fun begins.  a full week of swimming in the salty water but to me it doesn't bother.  all i can think about is the beach,  and how every waking moment all i want to do is reach.  reach into the sand and feel how it is cool,  but then,  it's time for the pool.  swimming there is fun,  i can't deny,  but it just doesn't fill the essentials of the ocean's eye.  at night as we walk along the beach and see giant crabs,  we all hope one won't give us a jab.  as the week draws to an end,  we find souvenirs souvenirs of shells and memeories dear.  then we start to pack up,  for the week is done but one thing i'll admit:we sure did have fun! and as i think of all we did i'm sure glad to still be a kid.  for if i was old,  i wouldn't have as much fun so i think its better to dig,  swim,  and throw sand while you're still young.

title: Suspense
author: kayla
text: come close,  my dear,  so you might hear what i have to say.   what you will hear will be as clear  as a bright sunny day in may.   my darling,  my dear,  what you will hear is something strange,  i know;  it is not about dogs,  kittens or gifts,  or the future,  or money,  or snow.   you want to know what i have to say,  you whine,  you snivel,  you beg,  and now,  right now,  i tell you now,  it is nothing but an egg!  you stare,  you smile,  you laugh,  you cry,  you don't understand,  but you don't know the meaning of what i hold in my hand.   an egg is an egg,  and will always be,  and though now you may laugh,  someday you will see.   that an egg is an egg.  it always was,  and was always meant to be.

title: A Winter Walk
author: keeley
text: a winter walk…    dec.  16/13       keeley   \ton a dark winter night,  the fat,  crystal-white snow fell softly.   it sparkled like stars in the moonlight.   the thick,  rich trickled down like majestic butterflies prancing through the spring meadow.   my toasty,  yet heavy boots dragged as i walked quietly along the long,  black road.   the carolers sounded beautiful in the distance,  like a rainbow after a storm.   my snow white,  peppermint gum was losing flavor.   it was bitter and pungent.  i spit it out!  the dry,  cold winter air grated on my parched throat.   the snow-covered pine smelt like warm tea.   thinking about tea,  an unearthly shiver ran down my spine like a cheetah!  the smell of ginger trickled out of the window like a waterfall of an elderly ladies house.  it filled the air with scents of joy and happiness!  the snowflakes hit my face and melted instantly.   i layed in the snow bank,  looking at the yellow fireballs in the sky.   millions of them.   the earth is finally asleep.  star by star,  snowflake by snowflake,  the earth sleeps as i finish my beautiful,  winter walk. .

text: there once was a man without much of a tan,  he was the man without the plan.    he had really dark hair and a crazy stare,  he made me care to dare.    he was fun,  wild as the sun.  he was the first one to call me hun.    he loved rock and was sort of a jock,  sometimes he ate dinner out of a box.    this is the story of a guy,  this story is true,  it is no lie.  his life passed on by and by,  and in my heart he will never die.

title: Grizzlies poem -2001
author: kelsey
text: don't you ever wonder who is the best? who plays the best,  looks the best,  and is kool takin' a test? we strut down the hall proud and tall.  we're not like you,  no we're much better,  we even look kooler wearing your sweater.  you wonder how we got so kool,  you wonder if you could do it too.  but no,  you can't because we're one of a kind,  if you tried to keep up you'd be left way behind.  we are the grizzlies as everyone knows,  whatever we say always goes.  we are the best,  we pass the test.  when we move we always groove.   we will beat you at any sport,  we are so kool on the basketball court.  you better stop in your tracks,  you better yeild,  we are really good on the baseball feild.  don't be surprised if your filled with dismay,  cuz we will whip your butt on any relay.  you better plan to be beaten by us,  you'll still be crying on the bus.  we know you want to be a grizzly too,  but you can't,  it's too late,  your already a fool.  so bow down to us grizzlies,  since we are the best,  now you be our servants while we get some rest! go grizzlies!

title: What it takes to be me
author: kelsey
text: i am the girl who wrote this poem,  if they don't like it i will surely show 'em,  just what it takes to be me.  my life is full of wonder,  i'm much different than most girls,  you are sure to grow fonder,  as i tell how my life unfearls.  when i was little we always sang,  forever all day and all night.  now i'm still singing and nothing has changed,  except for friends,  vocabulary,  and height.  music is a difficult buissiness,  you have to be the best.  you must know the right people and how to get in,  it surely is a test.  i can't wait to be famous,  but i think it will be a while.  i am just a young girl now and my homework is in a pile.  life will be great when my voice is found,  but patient i will be.  i will give the world a new sound,  you just wait and see.

title: MORNING

title: A Poem?
author: kelsey
text: sitting here once again.  alone of course,  without any friends.  writing this poem to pass the time.  coming up with it rhyme by rhyme.  word by word,  page by page.  i write poems to let out my rage.   i write about how i feel and what i see.   write about how and why i am me.   poems are good for the heart and soul.  at least thats how i feel and what i'm told.

title: You & Me
author: kelsey
text: you were my first kiss and will be my last.  you are all of my future and part of my past.  you make me who i am and what i want to be.   you keep me grounded but still let me soar free.  you were the man in all of my dreams,  ''i love you'',  ''i love you'',  is all my heart screams.   you may kiss soft and touch mild,  but everything about you makes me go wild.   you are the best man there is out there,  from your gentleness and humor right down to your care.  i know your the best,  the one for me.  but why do you want this girl,  what do you see?

title: Clock
author: kelsey
text: tick tock tick tock go the hands on the clock.   only five minutes untill the bell will ring  but there is one mysterious thing.  the minutes are dagging on longer than before.   i think i'll never exit through that door.  i quickly look at the clock to check the time it looks as though it's frozen as a block of ice and silent as a mime.  i turn around everyone is staring at the clock then suddenly i hear a loud knock.   a person steps through the doorway  and just one thing do they say-- your clock has stopped you can go home for today.

title: What If...
author: kiarra
text: what if the world was completely fair? what if we all had something to share? what if history repeats all over? what if someone found a five leaf clover? what if columbus never sailed the ocean blue? what if you could sail the ocean too? what if i were you and you were me? do you know how crazy that would be?! what if we never made mistakes? what if cars had no breaks? what if the world was just black and white? what if everyone had perfect sight? what if there was no day or night? what if we never had any light? what if there were no moon or sun? what if we were nice to everyone? what if red was blue and blue was brown? what if down was up and up was down? what if there was no such thing as school? what if we didnâ’t have to follow a rule? what if we had twenty-nine feet?  what if nobody on earth could ever eat? what if the world had not a single celebrity?  what if we all could learn some integrity? what if we were best friends with eachother? what if a book was named after your mother? what if your father had lost your brother? what if the book had no cover? what if dinosaurs were all plant eaters? what if i could run one thousand meters? what if this poem never stopped.  what if the crops were never cropped? these questions we ask,  (all the time) i think we forgot.  to think the other way.  what if it does not?

text: within the autumn morning mist,  by the fields of green,   animals of the world stir.  through the fields,  under trees in backyards,  they scurry and play like children on a sunny day,  unaware of change.  slowly a malignant force,  in countless towns of the world,  begins to spread.  within the rivers of the valley,   in the bodies of the fish,  illness obscures the vision of life.  soon on the farms,   in the earthworms and eggs,  everything is a shadow of death.  the trees of the forest no longer bloom,  and the flowers fail to expose their color.  the land in which the animals roam,  slowly becomes barren and known as the past.  in the pensive minds of the creatures they think,  what have we done to deserve this!

title: The oyster
author: krista
text: there once was an oyster who story i tell,  who found that some sand got in his shell.  it was only a grain,  but it gave him great pain.  for oysters have feelings although their so plain. now,  did he berate the harsh workings of fate that had brought him to such a deplorable state? did he curse at the government,  cry for election,  and claim that the sea should had given him protection? no-- he said to himself as he lay on a shell,  since i cannot remove it,  i shall try to improve it.  now the years have rolled around,  as the years always do,  as he came to his ultimate destiny--stew.  and the small grain of sand that had bothered him so was a beautiful pearl all richly aglow.  now the tail has a moral; for isn't a grand what an oyster can do with a morsel of sand.  what coulden't we do if we only begin with some of the things that get under our skin

title: I Run
author: kyle
text: i run.   the breeze holds me back but i break the chain.   i'm determined to win the race.   i will not fail,  i will not fall.   built on endurance,   fueled and won by speed.   freedom is my only need.   i run.   i run in winter's harshest snow,   the icy ground tells me ''go! go! go!''  i run in spring's heavy showers,   the refreshing sound gives me power,   and lets me run for many hours.   i like summer best,  despite the heat.   when i'm on my feet,  i can't be beat.   fall's crunch,  crunch,  crunch,   beneath my shoes,   assures me that i will not lose.   i am strong,  this much is true.   heaven and earth are with me,   so nothing can stop me.   i can bolt as quickly as lightning,   and run as long as i live.   i can't always win,   but i will always try my best.   i will run again and again.   never stopping too long to rest.   i run.   i run not to impress others,   but to stay healthy and active.   as long as i shall live.   staying fit and strong is ideal.   it is said that an object in motion,   stays in motion.   while an object at rest,   stays at rest.   the same is true for bodies.   we must keep them strong and growing,   and never let them fail.   it is essential for health,   and overrules knowledge and wealth.   i run.   i run because i love it,   and am never going to stop.   i run.

title: Idaho
author: kyle
text: the place to go is idaho! that's how the saying goes.  with the worlds longest boardwalk,  and the nation's best potatoes.   from priest lake,  down to thousand springs,  or craters of the moon.  raft the great snake river,  or buggy a sand dune.   come and fish for salmon or buy a bright flashlight,   to bike the great hiawatha,  the taft tunnels dark as night.   find a mountain stream,  and cast your favorite fly,  kayak down a river,  or hike up to the sky.   because we have some great big mountains,  a thousand or so lakes,   rivers that go underground and fluffy white snowflakes.   so ski up in sun valley,  or watch some mountain goats,  hells canyon is the deepest,  and theres a golf green that floats.   ride the world's longest gondola,  or tour a silver mine,  the place to go is idaho! i think it's mighty fine!

title: Wrong Desicions
author: laura
text: \ti was a straight a student,  that never had smoked,  drank or had done drugs.   i was a girl who had always done what her parents said,  hung out with people my parents liked.   but then i started high school.   there were a lot of new kids,  some good,  and some bad.   i met new people,  most of whom smoked drank and did drugs.   i told them iâ’d think about it and i didnâ’t think long enough.   i tried smoking i liked it like candy.   i tried drinking i liked it like pop.   and before long i was one of those people i said i would never be.    then it was clear to me i had chose the wrong friends.   i knew what i did was wrong,  but i thought it was the way.   i didnâ’t tell my parents because i knew theyâ’d freak.   and pretty soon my habits were two packs a day.   my friends said that it was okay and that everyone does it,  but they were wrong not everyone does it.   but i kept on going.   then pretty soon my parents found out they said they knew that this would happen.   my mom said that she was like this once when she was a teenager and that her parents let her figure it out that was she did was wrong on her own.   so thatâ’s what my parents did.   it didnâ’t work i just kept going farther and farther.   my girlfriends started skipping school getting caught by the cops.   then suddenly it hit me that sure i was really popular but i was killing myself bit by bit.   of course i tried to stop but i had gone so far i couldnâ’t.   my parents wanted to help me,  and i wanted them to but i didnâ’t want to actually tell them they were right and i was wrong.   but i am doing better now,  i am down to one cigarette a week and i have quit drinking.   and now i think to myself what if i had kept doing what i was doing.   where would i be?  my old friends are still partying like never before,  all but one of my friends,  mya.   mya told me that she wanted to quit but didnâ’t know how.   so i said i would help her.   now mya and i are doing great we have completely stopped drinking and smoking.   we are glad we stopped because we were only 16 and that is way to young to die.

title: Moonlight
author: laura
text: i sit outside,   on a whitewashed porch.   a brush in one hand,   and an empty canvas,  lit by a torch.    i have sat here,   through the hues of twilight.   watching as the last rays of rainbow,   fade into a black,  empty night.    i have watched the stars appear and twinkle,   i have heard the barn owlâ’s hoots.   i can taste the scent of an evening primrose,   still,  i watch as the sky puts on its dark suit.    a gust of wind pushes a cloud away,   here she comes finally,  beautiful as ever.   a pale circle of light against a colorless sky,   here comes the moon,  gleaming silver.    this was the moment i had been waiting for,   this was the scene i had sought for so long.   but now,  sitting here,  i cannot even raise my brush,   for the beauty of silver moonlight evades any description,  lifelong.

text: you walk down the street and with everyone you meet,  they all look the same, with backward hats,  baggy shorts,  untied shows,  tie-die shirts.  shiny black boots, handsome suits, a tight dress,  hairs a mess.  dressed all fancy with that purse,  just 'cause their beautiful,  people let them first.  diamond rings,  pretty things, unbuttoned shirts,  old fashioned skirts.  people try to be wannabes other than who they are; but in the inside,  they're different;  they'll always be their own star.  in that big blue sky,  theres enough room for all the people to fly.

title: What if...

title: Hope
author: lindsay
text: hope is a way to cope.   when times get hard,  we reach out to hope.    looking for comfort,  like a best friend.    hope carries us through a rough day.   she holds us up when we are about to fall down.   we donâ’t give up,  desperate to see hope again.   hope gives us a reason to keep trying.    hope is peering out of the window on a rainy day,   waiting for sunshine.   hope is holding a sick personâ’s hand,   telling her it will get better.    beside hope is denial.   they are like cousins,  though one is  more demanding and indelicate.      denial is stubborn,   forcing our minds to not believe bad news.   hope is encouraging,   suggesting we focus on the positive.    but behind both ways of coping,   there is doubt.   it is easier to let the doubt overcome the hope.   but if we did that,  we would lose the comfort of a best friend  and have to sulk through our hardships alone.   so we keeping holding on to hope,  leaning on its shoulder  and following its path of friendship.

title: Dancing
author: lindsay
text: the light hits them and many different colors dance off of them.   a bead curtain hanging in an entrance to the room,  the purple beads dance and shimmer before your eyes drawing you into the picture that is the beads.  then someone walks through them and pushes them aside easily,  the beads sway quickly back and forth \tthey slow then as though to catch their breath.  all but several strands who cannot give up the dance that they adore.  they continue to dance and sway with the slightest movements.  as though they werenâ’t moving at all.  the noise of slight swishes as the beads continue to dance,  running into one another frantically as if they were forcing themselves to lead on that ecstatic dance forever.  eventually they bring their beautiful dance to a halt,  waiting for the next opportunity they have to continue the dance that they love.

title: A Chihuahua on my Head
author: lindsay
text: when i awoke one morning,   a chihuahua sat on my head.  i asked,  â“what are you doing there?â” it looked at me and said,  â“i was walking past your window and when i looked inside,   you were laying there on your bed,  you were laying on your side. â” â“ i donâ’t have anywhere else to go,  so i thought it would be okay,  if i came in and joined your slumber on this cold day. â” when i sat up it was raining outside and i didnâ’t know what to say,   as ample amounts of rained poured down.  iâ’d never seen so much rain in my life and i didnâ’t know what to do,  then all of a sudden i sat up and found that i had to get up too i was almost late for school.  i jumped up and knocked the little dog off,  he landed with a squeal and yelled in my ear: â“what did you do that for?!â” â“i didnâ’t mean to. â” i started to say,  but it was too late,  that little dog was already gone.  to sit on someone elseâ’s head that day.

title: My Dog

title: Conflicts
author: lindsay
text: our world is changing now,  for everyone is resulting in conflict.  people have died for me and my pride,  and they needn't have.  not often do i wonder,  what happens to them,  but i should,  for they matter more than i.  across the sea in a desert land,  they sit and wait for another fight.  but i know they dream of their sweethearts back home,  and the day they are awarded for their actions.  if you saw through their eyes what they see,  you would be amazed at them.  for courage is not always what people do,  but what people are willing to do,  too.

title: A Dream is only a Dream

title: Troubled Mind
author: lindsay
text: i want to go inside a brick wall      and never come out.    it seems like nobody hears me      when i cry and shout.    nobody likes me,  nobody cares.    should you come near me,      no one else dares!   i want to go inside a brick wall.    i feel like i slipped off a cliff     and continue to fall.    i t's like a bad dream     and i'll never wake up,   ahhhhhh,  can't you hear me?      please make it stop.   i want to go inside a brick wall     and cry my eyes out.  even though my mom always told me    it's not good to pout.  i want to get all my feelings out     right then and there,  i need to find out what to do with my life    how,  when,  and where.   i have now gone inside my heart    and seen the light.  i know know i can make it    with god as a guide and all my might.  i am glad i didn't do     what i know i'd regret.  for i have made goals    which i intend to somehow get.

title: Cardboard Tears
author: lindsey
text: with tears as stone,  with a cold,  cracked heart,  with the wind of ice,   the rain poured in  with my cardboard blanket,  with my mattress of cement,  with my cup holding thirty-nine cents,   the hail storm  my lips faded blue,  my shirt ripped,   my cardboard blanket,  now wet paper,  dripping and crying,  until four a. m.   i awoke on a bed looking like a queen  but then,   just like that,  my heart broke  a child next to me,  my former self,  with thirty-nine cents,  looked up to me,  crying with hope,  begging for money  how could i refuse,  i went for my cup-  i awoke,  now it is five a. m.  and my cardboard blanket has rolled away. . .  into the icy wind.

title: Eon
author: lisa marie
text: the clouds stretch,  elongated in the sky,  holding shut the heavenly gates.  the canyons sleep,  mid-snarl,  abandoned rocks decorate the mountains,  sleepily watching trees leap across the gullies,  tearing through the earth.  mountain climbers flash by,  gone,  unseen,  unoticed.   trees reach for the sky,  mocking the stones.  the stones mock them when they are gone,  changing with the rolling seasons.  luminous leaves glowing gold,  then slipping quickly back to green,  lauging at the stars' illusions.

title: Death
author: livie
text: she walked down the corridor,  death took her by the hand,  fate took her by the shoulder but she did not understand.   she walked down the staircase,  when she came face to face,  with an angel shining amazingly,  she'd met her saving grace.   she walked into the car park,  and watched the monster coming,  that was when she met death,  there was no time for running.

title: A Tranquil Beach
author: livie
text: the moonlight dances,  on the calm and silent beach,  while an old can is left,  deserted and alone.  the pandemonium,  from a few hours earlier,  has lost,  in a battle against tranquillity.  little kids sandcastles,  have been guzzled up by the hungry waves,  as they make their way up the land,   which cannot fight back.  it is a beautiful picture,  not as rowdy as before,  but a friendly silence,  as peacefulness reins the beach.

title: Spring is Alive
author: logan
text: spring is flower-beautiful,   when roses bloom.  it's a fragrance so sweet ,  i can taste them blush  as they dance in the wind  spring is young,  when children play hide-and-seek.  i can hear their laughter for miles.  i can see their smiles like the sun shines,         as they b o u n c e about.    spring is loverluscious  when lovers are about.  kissing and dreaming of futures.  i can feel the love across the park,  as their affection  is gratified by one another.   spring is alive  when babies are born  as when children play,  and when lovers dream,  and the thought of liveliness  brings tears from the sky.

title: The Path Change
author: luanne
text: you can see it in their eyes,  the young,  and the old.  itâ’s the terror,  the regret,  the stories being told.  itâ’s being afraid of what will become,  when everyone is fighting turning everyone down.    moms and dads never see their kids grow up.  children never have an idol to look up to.  families and friends never see the elders or the babies crying and living in pain.  weâ’ll lose what we need,  to get what we want  is it really worth it? changing the world when weâ’ve always been this way.  what does it matter? whoâ’s willing to give up everything,  to take one step closer into death? are you ready to be separate from the rest?  why not just start over?  create new; stop the old way of living.  forgetting our past,  and just relaxing.  itâ’s only our future,  sure thatâ’s what you could say.  what more is it really anyway? we all come,  we all go,  for what who cares,  when who knows? but are you really ready to die in a never-ending battle with life?  itâ’s not just you and me canâ’t you see? open your eyes.  look with your heart.  smile with your actions,  breath with all your feelings.  love with your life.    we were given the world.  we turned it great.  yet our sorrow and need to discriminate,  will end us.  unless we all vow,  to stop killing our own,  to get off the streets,  and make a difference.  just remember what you do,  doesnâ’t only effect you!
